{
    "analysis": "From prior steps: Metric analysis (global P95 before window) found many sparse KPIs with P95==0 (ignore), and credible sustained anomalies in socket KPIs across many services—checkoutservice/socket and several others stayed at or above their P95 during the window; frontend/socket had a large spike (max=27) at 2024-01-19T18:14:00Z. Trace duration analysis (global P95 before window) found brief duration spikes (anomaly_count=2) with the most notable being frontend-related latency around 2024-01-19T18:10:00Z: root→frontend and frontend→checkout spans show elevated durations (max ~0.692s for frontend trace_p95 and ~0.345s for frontend→checkout). These findings together point toward a network/socket-related issue affecting request handling around ~18:10–18:14, with frontend and checkout involved. To localize the root-cause service and reason we must now inspect logs (log.csv and error_logs.csv): compute global thresholds for log KPIs, then check the incident window for log.error_count or other log signals that coincide with the socket/latency anomalies (earliest timestamps and counts). This will help confirm whether the failure reason is socket errors/network issues or something else (e.g., downstream service slowness).",
